						<summary>

						<p>On the south wall, central shrine, Avaṉisundarēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Year 14: 985 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Records that the queen of Uttamachōḷa, Vīranārāyaṇiyār consecrated the image of Avaṉisundara along with a halo <hi rend="italic">(prabhai)</hi> and pedestal for the purpose of procession during the festival on the day of <hi rend="italic">viśākham</hi> in the month of <hi rend="italic">vaikāśi</hi> in the temple of Avanīśvaram at Pāchchil in Maḻa-nāḍu.</p>						

